					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1540605669 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Oct 2018 02:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4040556">
									

<p>I guess this is kind of a format experiment. It was a little difficult to balance having a narrative structure (the typical exposition-to-resolution timeline) with the inherently chaotic structure of conversations in a web forum, but it is what it is, I rearranged the comments several times until I thought they were in the right places for narrative layout, and now I'm coldposting it. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯</p>
<p>It's definitely a <em>short</em> story, which is something I typically have trouble producing, as we have seen from most of my long-ass works in this canon alone as well as elsewhere.</p>
<hr />
<p><sub>Also&#8230; related to the subject matter&#8230; Hey kids, IRL talk here, did you <a href="https://vote.gov/">vote?</a> You can <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/10/04/us/politics/early-vote-elections.html">vote early you know.</a> Voting is important; please do it!</sub></p>

