			<div class="content" id="post-content-4040832">
									

<p>Having a single designated social media guy for a toxic community (whether it be League of Legends, Overwatch, Runescape or the Broken Masquerade-verse) is a mistake, because 1) all fuck-ups are going to be blamed on them 2) they're going to get the brunt of the hatred from everyone on the sub and get them frustrated and 3) that frustration is going to lead to the social media guy blowing up and making everyone involved look like asses.</p>
<p>When game devs to post on the Overwatch or League or RS subreddits, it's usually in turns. You can tell that being yelled at by people with the maturity of twelve-year-olds when it comes to a game they allegedly love gets to them.</p>

