    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4044139">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4044139">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4044139)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4044139">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captainbacon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938198); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3938198&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203356" alt="CaptainBacon" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3938198)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captainbacon" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3938198); return false;" >CaptainBacon</a></span> <span class="odate time_1540871078 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Oct 2018 03:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4044139">
									

<p>I actually enjoy the setting even more for the sudden nature of the Broken Masquerade. Would a Foundation that had always been in the open have been as cold and secretive as the Foundation we're all familiar with? And what is the Foundation in the absence of dying in the dark or &quot;shut up and calculate&quot; ethics?</p>
<p>The premise of Broken Masquerade isn't so much &quot;what if people knew about the Foundation?&quot; as it is &quot;What if everything went to hell and it all came to light?&quot;, which I find much more compelling. Certainly an &quot;Absent Masquerade&quot; canon would be interesting, but probably more bureaucratic and Kafkaesque than Broken Masquerade is.</p>

							</div>

								
					
						<div class="options">
				
													<strong><a href="javascript:;" onclick="postReply(event,4044139)" class="btn btn-primary btn-small btn-sm">Reply</a></strong> 
