		<div class="post" id="post-4044598">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4044598)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4044598">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1540906891 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Oct 2018 13:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4044598">
									

<p>Yeah, fair, and I didn't phrase that the best. By &quot;inherently part of the setting and not even explained&quot; I meant &quot;no one explains how the secrecy was blown, we just know that it was.&quot; But maybe that'd be a cop-out.</p>

							</div>

								
					
