		<div class="post" id="post-4044831">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4044831)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4044831">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mickeyten" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4444390); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4444390&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203356" alt="mickeyten" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4444390)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mickeyten" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4444390); return false;" >mickeyten</a></span> <span class="odate time_1540920203 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Oct 2018 17:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4044831">
									

<p>100% agree. Doesn't stop me from enjoying Broken Masquerade, but the setup is <em>so</em> OTT and it would probably be a bit more grounded and intriguing if the readers and contributors were able to play with the mystery of why the masquerade failed.</p>
<p>BTW, I associate you so strongly with this canon, I often forget you <em>didn't</em> create it. Consider that a compliment!</p>

							</div>

								
